{
  "texts": [
    "In this scenario, a possible solution could involve the development of an Online Transfer Learning (OTL) strategy.",
    "According to this strategy, the weights of the neural networks are initialised to values obtained for the source building and then further fine-tuned on the target building while the DRL agent actively controls the system.",
    "The weight-initialisation helps retain the acquired knowledge from the source building in cases where certain boundary conditions match those of the target building.",
    "Subsequently, fine-tuning the control policy would be necessary to adapt to the new conditions (e.g., energy systems) present in the target buildings.",
    "However, this procedure is not always feasible as the presence of different energy systems leads to different state and/or action spaces among DRL controllers implemented in different buildings, thereby limiting the application of the weight-initialisation technique."
  ]
}